2026-04-14 08:16:58,973 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: We have inspected the workbook. It contains a single sheet with 13 columns; column C (index 3) holds the Name, column I (index 9) holds the Entry Time, and column M (index 13) is the "Max" column where the user wants a label indicating whether the row’s Entry Time is the latest for that Name.  

Excel 2013 does not have MAXIFS, so we need an array formula that compares each row’s Entry Time to the maximum Entry Time for the same Name:

```
=IF(I2=MAX(IF($C$2:$C$41=C2,$I$2:$I$41)), "Latest", "Not Latest")
```

Entered with Ctrl+Shift+Enter (CSE). The formula uses absolute ranges covering all data rows (row 2 to max_row). We will write this formula into every cell of column M (the "Max" column) for rows 2 through max_row, overwriting any existing values.  

After writing, we will:
1. Save the workbook to the output directory.
2. Call `await recalculate(output_path)` to evaluate the formulas.
3. Reload the workbook with `data_only=True` and print a few sample results to confirm the labels appear as expected.

The following code performs these steps.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter

# Paths
input_path = input_spreadsheet  # provided variable
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/"
output_path = output_dir + "1_58723_init.xlsx"

# Load workbook (keep formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb.active  # assume single sheet

# Determine data range (skip header row)
first_data_row = 2
max_row = ws.max_row
max_col = ws.max_column

# Column indices
col_name = 3   # C
col_entry = 9  # I
col_max = 13   # M (header "Max")

# Write array formula into each cell of column M
for r in range(first_data_row, max_row + 1):
    # Build absolute range strings based on max_row
    name_range = f"$C${first_data_row}:$C${max_row}"
    entry_range = f"$I${first_data_row}:$I${max_row}"
    formula = f'=IF(I{r}=MAX(IF({name_range}=C{r},{entry_range})), "Latest", "Not Latest")'
    ws.cell(row=r, column=col_max).value = formula

# Save the workbook to the output location
wb.save(output_path)
print("Workbook saved with formulas to:", output_path)

# Recalculate formulas using the provided tool
recalc_result = await recalculate(output_path)
print("Recalculate result:", recalc_result)

# Reload the workbook with calculated values (data_only=True)
wb_data = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_data = wb_data.active

# Print a few sample rows to verify the output
print("\nSample verification (rows 2-6):")
for r in range(2, min(7, ws_data.max_row + 1)):
    name = ws_data.cell(row=r, column=col_name).value
    entry = ws_data.cell(row=r, column=col_entry).value
    label = ws_data.cell(row=r, column=col_max).value
    print(f"Row {r}: Name={name}, Entry={entry}, MaxLabel={label}")

# Also check the last few rows
print("\nSample verification (last 5 rows):")
for r in range(max(ws_data.max_row - 4, 2), ws_data.max_row + 1):
    name = ws_data.cell(row=r, column=col_name).value
    entry = ws_data.cell(row=r, column=col_entry).value
    label = ws_data.cell(row=r, column=col_max).value
    print(f"Row {r}: Name={name}, Entry={entry}, MaxLabel={label}")
```
